---
description: Project coding standards for Next.js app
alwaysApply: true
---

- Use TypeScript for all application code.
- Keep modules cohesive and avoid deeply nested logic in components.
- Prefer explicit naming for server/client boundaries.
- Add or update tests for changed behavior.
- Keep changes small and focused; avoid unrelated refactors in the same PR.
- If behavior, API contract, or setup changes, update docs in the same change.

## Example

```ts
// Good: focused module with explicit server boundary and testable logic.
export async function getProfileById(userId: string) {
  if (!userId) throw new Error("userId required");
  return db.profile.findUnique({ where: { userId } });
}

// Bad: mixes unrelated behavior and weak naming.
export async function doStuff(a: string) {
  // fetch profile + send email + mutate settings in one function
}
```
